=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Vaping Enforcement
Date: 1 March 2023
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Oral Answer)
Topic: Synergising enforcement against vaping

Summary:

- Question:
  Whether MOH will consider synergising enforcement capabilities of the Health Sciences Authority (HSA) with the National Environment Agency (NEA) to present a common front against vapers and those breaching vaping regulations.

- MOH Response:
  1. MOH adopts a multi-pronged approach addressing vaping:
     - Enforcement
     - Public education
  2. Cross-agency enforcement pilot:
     - HSA and NEA are collaborating.
     - NEA enforcement officers are piloted to enforce against vaping offences in addition to their existing duties.
  
Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)
- Health Sciences Authority (HSA)
- National Environment Agency (NEA)

Key Concepts:
- Multi-agency enforcement
- Cross enforcement pilot
- Integrated approach to address vaping and regulatory breaches
